  "title": "#SG United Mid-Career Pathways Programme - Accounts Executive",
  "description": "<p>Key Responsibilities: <br />1.  Record Keeping:  Maintain accurate financial records, processing of Accounts Payables and Receivables.</p><p>2.  Monitor customer payments and follow up on outstanding receivables.</p><p>3.  Reporting:  Assist in preparing monthly, quarterly and annual financial reports as well as audit support activities.</p><p>4.  Month-end:  Support month-end closing, prepare account reconciliations & bank reconciliations, and prepare financial schedules.                                                                                                                                                         </p><p>5.  Compliance:  Maintain complete records of all financial transactions.  Assist in preparing documents for audits, tax submissions and statutory requirements.<br /></p><p>Requirements:<br />1.  Diploma or Degree in Accounting, Finance, or a related field.<br />2.  Project management and time management.<br />3.  Analytical and problem-solving abilities.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  4.  Attention to details.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              5.  Data entry and records management.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            6.  Ability to meet deadlines and work independently or within a finance team.<br />7.  Advanced proficiency in Microsoft Office (Excel, Word & Powerpoint), and Google Sheets for data analysis.</p><p><br />Government Support:  SG United Mid-Career Pathways Programme <br />Position:  Accounts Executive<br />Duration:  6 months</p>",
